    "body": "Filters are stored in memory. If you restart geth these filters are lost and you need to recreate the filter and poll with the new one. This is true for `eth_getFilterChanges` and `eth_getFilterLogs`. Exception is `eth_getLogs` that doesn't accept a filter id but instead the full criteria. This method won't give you the changes but all (stored) logs that match the given criteria.\n\n> It is written that filters are permanent\n\nWhere did you find this?\n",
